textBeforeTable: Declension of gās Declension[edit] a goose gās f Noun[edit] From Proto-Germanic *gans, whence also Old English gōs, Old Frisian gōs, Old High German gans, Old Norse gás. Ultimately from Proto-Indo-European *ǵʰans-. Etymology[edit] gōs Alternative forms[edit] Old Saxon[edit] (Jersey) chap gas m (plural gas) Noun[edit] From Old French gars, nominative singular form of garçon. Etymology[edit] Norman[edit] rafsi of ganse.
textAfterTable: Descendants[edit] Low German: Goos Rohingya[edit] Etymology[edit] From Bengali.
